{{doc/start}}
Takes a single parameter and provides a link to something accompanied by a 20px image of it.

For this template to work, there must be a png image with the same name of the page you are trying to link to.

Optionally define a second parameter to change the name of the item.

==Usage==
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">
{{ItemLink|Assembler I}}
{{ItemLink|Assembler II|Second-Level Assembler}}
</syntaxhighlight>
{{ItemLink|Assembler I}}<br/>
{{ItemLink|Assembler II|Second-Level Assembler}}

===Parameters===
* <code>1</code> defines the name and image, adding content equivalent to <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">[[File:{{{1}}}.png|20x20px|link={{{1}}}]] [[{{{1}}}]]</syntaxhighlight>.
* <code>2</code> (optional) provides alternate text on the link. If given, the template will instead add content equivalent to <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">[[File:{{{1}}}.png|20x20px|link={{{1}}}]] [[{{{1}}}|{{{2}}}]]</syntaxhighlight>.

===TemplateData===
